Sustainability of our planet and its natural resources has come under the spotlight for the past number of years as the detrimental effects  of global warming and climate change become evident. Droughts, floods and wildfires are all a manifestation of society, with a carbon footprint that is too large for the planet to bear. We also need to ask whether there is a causal relationship between increasing environmental pressure and outbreaks of pandemic diseases like Covid-19. With this in mind, what responsibility do business and industry bear  in mitigating the effects of climate change on the environment, society and the economy? Join the TimesLive Dialogues and the Gautrain Management Agency  as they examine  the importance of contributing to the green economy, and how the Gautrain is doing its part to become carbon neutral. In this discussion, moderated by Joanne Joseph, the panellists include: WATCH THE DISCUSSION: